A tragic incident unfolded when a suicidal man left his car on train tracks near Los Angeles, causing a collision that killed 10 and injured over 100.
The chaotic scene involved derailed trains, passengers jumping to safety, and a citywide alert for emergency response.
The man, identified as Juan Manuel Alvarez, faced charges for the deadly outcome of his failed suicide attempt.
The impact was described as the worst train wreck since 1999, prompting calls for enhanced rail safety measures.
Alvarez's motives, troubled past, and subsequent actions added layers of complexity to the devastating event.
